  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>white long grain rice</strong> until the water runs clear, then add it to a pot with a lid with 175ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat </p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked </p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>pork loin steaks </strong>dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub them with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, the<strong> five-spice mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> spiced pork loin steaks</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until they're browned and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pork is cooking, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Wash, then rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar </strong>and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Once the pork is cooked, reduce the heat to low and add the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for a further 1 min, turning the pork steaks several times until they're nicely coated</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and set aside to rest for a couple of min – these are your <strong>Taiwanese-style pork steaks</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong>, <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and cook, covered for 3-4 min or until tender – these are your <strong>sesame greens</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the veg is cooking, trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Roughly chop the <strong>peanuts </strong>(or bash them in their bag!)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>rested Taiwanese-style pork steaks </strong>over the<strong> cooked rice </strong>with the <strong>sesame greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over any<strong> remaining hoisin sauce</strong> from the pan and garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and <strong>chopped peanuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
